  abstract={With the continuous development of smart power grid, the operation mode of substation is gradually complex, and the operation condition of transmission and transformation equipment fluctuates greatly. However, the traditional intelligent robot inspection method of substation may have some problems, such as limited monitoring scope, redundant inspection path and untargeted monitoring, which cannot meet the inspection requirements. Therefore, this paper proposes an operation and maintenance strategy based on A* algorithm to inspect substation with multi-group intelligent robots and Unmanned Aerial Vehicle (UAV). First according to the importance of the substation equipment instrument, failure rate and determine the fault happens on the system the influence degree of the equipment required for monitoring frequency, thus realize monitoring equipment hierarchies, and based on the substation physical environment monitoring division, according to the equipment level in each area, A* algorithm is adopted to improve the variety of path planning. Matlab simulation shows that compared with the traditional full-area substation inspection strategy, this method can effectively reduce the inspection time, shorten the path length, and guarantee the full coverage of all monitoring task points while taking into account the monitoring frequency required by each equipment. Simulation results show that the proposed method has good security and timeliness, and has high application value in substation inspection planning.},
